# Copy to the repo root as `.env` (Docker Compose loads it automatically):
#   cp .env.integration.example .env
# Full checklist: docs/INTEGRATION_STARTUP.md
# Then rebuild so Next.js embeds NEXT_PUBLIC_* correctly:
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.integration.yml up -d --build
#
# Replace the host with your public IP/DNS (e.g. sslip.io). Open security groups for 3000 and 8000.
#
# EC2: ``scripts/deploy-ec2.sh`` derives NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL from DEVNEST_FRONTEND_PUBLIC_BASE_URL
# when NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL is unset (fixes browsers still calling localhost:8000).
#
# --- Database (integration / EC2) ---
# RDS / GitHub Actions: use a **single-line SQLAlchemy** URL (NOT libpq ``host=... port=... dbname=...``).
# Example (redact password in real files):
#   postgresql+psycopg://USER:PASSWORD@HOST.rds.amazonaws.com:5432/devnest?sslmode=require
# CI writes ``DATABASE_URL``, ``DEVNEST_COMPOSE_DATABASE_URL``, and ``DEVNEST_DATABASE_URL`` to the same value
# via ``scripts/write_integration_deploy_env.py``. For bundled Postgres, omit DB keys.
# App + Alembic resolve the same URL via ``get_settings().database_url`` (``DEVNEST_DATABASE_URL`` wins over
# ``DATABASE_URL`` if they ever differ).

DEVNEST_FRONTEND_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:8000
# Remote workspace URLs must resolve from the browser to Traefik on this host.
DEVNEST_BASE_DOMAIN=98-92-163-201.sslip.io
DEVNEST_GATEWAY_PUBLIC_SCHEME=http
DEVNEST_GATEWAY_PUBLIC_PORT=9081
#
# OAuth is enabled only when the client id, client secret, and public callback base URL are all set.
# In integration/EC2, the backend defaults GITHUB_OAUTH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL / GCLOUD_OAUTH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL
# from DEVNEST_FRONTEND_PUBLIC_BASE_URL when those are unset or loopback-only.
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# OAUTH_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Optional explicit overrides if callbacks should use a different public base:
# GITHUB_OAUTH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:3000
# GCLOUD_OAUTH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://98-92-163-201.sslip.io:3000
#
# Optional short-lived auth/RDS debugging (no secrets in responses):
#   DEVNEST_AUTH_DIAGNOSTICS=true  → backend GET /internal/devnest-auth-diagnostics
#   Same on the frontend service → GET /api/internal/devnest-diagnostics (Next→FastAPI probe).
# DEVNEST_AUTH_DIAGNOSTICS=
#
# --- Optional fail-fast (backend + workspace-worker; default false in compose) ---
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_EXTERNAL_POSTGRES=true  → abort if DB host resolves to bundled service name ``postgres``
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_REMOTE_GATEWAY_CLIENTS=true  → abort if DEVNEST_BASE_DOMAIN is app.lvh.me / app.devnest.local
# ``scripts/deploy-ec2.sh`` sets both when DATABASE_URL is set for RDS deploys.
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_EXTERNAL_POSTGRES=
# DEVNEST_EXPECT_REMOTE_GATEWAY_CLIENTS=
#
# --- Snapshot archive storage (live workspace files stay on bind mounts) ---
# Local/dev (bundled Postgres, no DEVNEST_EXPECT_* flags): omit snapshot vars → local filesystem snapshots.
#
# EC2 / RDS (``scripts/deploy-ec2.sh`` sets DEVNEST_EXPECT_EXTERNAL_POSTGRES + DEVNEST_EXPECT_REMOTE_GATEWAY_CLIENTS
# when DATABASE_URL is set): you MUST use S3 — backend and workspace-worker fail startup otherwise.
# DEVNEST_SNAPSHOT_STORAGE_PROVIDER=s3
# DEVNEST_S3_SNAPSHOT_BUCKET=your-devnest-snapshots-bucket
# DEVNEST_S3_SNAPSHOT_PREFIX=devnest-snapshots
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# Optional if you want a fixed local staging path for S3 upload/download temp archives:
# DEVNEST_SNAPSHOT_TEMP_DIR=/var/lib/devnest/snapshot-staging
